window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>After a successful revolt in 1846 that reversed the roles of slaves and masters, modern-day America is now dominated by a wealthy, Black ruling class, and Whites are dealing with decades of oppression and prejudice.</p> <p>When his father, a civil rights attorney, is killed after defending a White man, 17-year-old Willie Gibbons is forced to move to Michigan with his uncle and thrust into the heart of the racial divide. The search for his father's killer lands Willie on the wrong side of a powerful and shadowy black supremacist group known as The Crown, a dangerous place for any man - Black or White.</p> <p><i>The Crown Lord</i> is a stark and jarring look at race, class, and the American Dream that will keep listeners on edge.</p>"; 
